<p>Thereâ€™s a sweet little niche in the stationery world for everyday-carry (<span class="small-caps">EDC</span>) notebooks.</p>
<p>Field Notes, Moleskine, Rite in the Rain, Leuchtturm1917, Rhodia, good olâ€™ Spirax, and so many more. Youâ€™ll find them in stores and on websites guaranteed to make your paper-loving mouth water! Whatever your preference, you can find it in an <span class="small-caps">A6</span> or <span class="small-caps">A7</span> size notebook: lines, grid, blank, stapled, coil, stitched.</p>
<p>Iâ€™ve used (and loved) many of those little cuties, but thereâ€™s a new contender for paper notes thatâ€™s free of the pressure a proper notebook can imply, and it doesnâ€™t cost a thing.</p>
<p><strong>Always with you</strong></p>
<p>Introducing what I have affectionately dubbed my One-Page Notebook (<span class="small-caps">1PN</span>). The One-Page Notebook is simply a regular sheet of paper, folded in half two to three times. Itâ€™s big enough to write on without needing a card cover, and small enough to fit in a pocket or in whatever youâ€™re using to carry your stuff.</p>
<p>If youâ€™ve ever played around with <a href="https://www.43folders.com/2004/09/03/introducing-the-hipster-pda" target="_blank">The Hipster <span class="small-caps">PDA</span></a> concept (another gift from <a href="https://ellanew.com/2025/08/20/merlin-mann-wisdom-project" title="wikilink">Merlin Mann</a> to the world), the <span class="small-caps">1PN</span> might feel somewhat familiar. The One-Page Notebook is what The Hipster <span class="small-caps">PDA</span> might look like when itâ€™s on holiday.</p>
<p><a href="https://ellanew.com/2023/08/28/ptpl-067-edc-mother-ship-explorer-pod" title="wikilink">My every day carry (<span class="small-caps">EDC</span>) is a Bellroy crossbody bag</a>. Thereâ€™s room for an <span class="small-caps">A6</span> notebook in the centre section, but <span class="small-caps">A7</span> fits nicely into one of the inner pouches so thatâ€™s the size I use. My current notebook is an el-cheapo no-name spiral top lined pad with a translucent plastic cover, but itâ€™s not alone in there! Tucked neatly behind it is my sweet little <span class="small-caps">1PN</span>.</p>
